授業の到達目標:
At the end of this course students will:
1) enhance their skills of expansion reading and research;
2) expand their knowledge on topics from an interdisciplinary perspective;
3) develop an understanding of and appreciation for the inter-relatedness and complexity of issues faced by the individual and society;
4) develop critical thinking skills and be able to formulate opinions on topics studied;
5) and organically acquire an activist and aesthetic attitude towards public speeches as powerful tools to not only inspire but also change minds and hearts.

